# Plan: Add PulseBoard Channel Plugin

## Context

PulseBoard is a fictional real-time bulletin board messaging platform. Users post messages to named "boards" (group chats, analogous to IRC channels or Slack channels) and send direct messages to other users. This plan adds a new first-party channel plugin under `extensions/pulseboard/`, following the exact structural and naming conventions of existing plugins like Nostr (simpler, single-account, DM-focused) and IRC (supports both `direct` and `group` chat types).

**Key characteristics:**
- Plugin ID: `pulseboard`
- Chat types: `["direct", "group"]`
- Text chunk limit: 4000 characters
- Auth: API token (`channels.pulseboard.apiToken`)
- Direct targets: `@username`
- Board (group) targets: `#board-name`
- DM policy: default `"pairing"` (same as Nostr/IRC)
- Delivery mode: `"direct"`
- No external npm dependencies (fictional platform → stub client)

**Constraint:** Only create new files under `extensions/pulseboard/`. Zero changes to existing files.

---

## Naming Invariants

These must all align to pass `src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts`:

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| Directory | `extensions/pulseboard/` |
